How do Gatland and Jones compare? That's easy - one's shrewd the other's rude.And, while we're on the subject, of the upcoming England-Wales clash, lets have some realism.The honeymoon period continues for the boorish Australian windbag, who is still suffering an element of disbelief, given his sudden prosperity from almost down-and-out to being put in charge of the richest rugby union team in the world, with 250,000 players to choose from, and a seven-figure salary to boot. With three 'wins' out of three everything in the garden appears rosy. Or does it? Certainly Jones has come up smelling of roses so far, but if the truth be known, and it is, he has only really survived by the skin of his teeth (for example, fortuitous decisions on the part of the referee and TMO against Ireland).The 'marriage' has not yet been consummated - the fatuous grin that Jones wears is based on the fact that he continues to ride ( in a good way of course) Lady Luck. Sadly, though, his luck is about to run out. The bookies earn their living by getting it right, and have installed the Welsh as hot favourites for this weekend's encounter that will almost certainly determine the Six Nations championship. So, Bang goes the Triple Crown....the Grand Slam...and England's first Six Nations tournament success since 2011 ( under Martin Johnson) but there's good news, as England will secure second place again, assuming the French don't put the boot in in Paris. Old habits die hard.



